# Windows Server 2022 — Domain Controller Configuration

Complete setup for Windows Server 2022 as the domain controller managing `corp.local` domain.

---

## Installation & Network Setup

### Create the VM

| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| **Name** | DC01 |
| **RAM** | 4096 MB |
| **CPU** | 2 cores |
| **Disk** | 60 GB |
| **Network** | Host-only Adapter → vboxnet0 |

Boot from Windows Server 2022 ISO, select Desktop Experience edition, and complete installation. Set Administrator password and rename computer to **DC01**.

### Configure Static IP Address

The domain controller must have a fixed IP — if it changes, the entire domain breaks.

```powershell
New-NetIPAddress -InterfaceAlias Ethernet -IPAddress 192.168.10.10 -PrefixLength 24 -DefaultGateway 192.168.10.1
```

Set DNS to point to itself (DC01 becomes the DNS server after AD install):

```powershell
Set-DnsClientServerAddress -InterfaceAlias Ethernet -ServerAddresses 127.0.0.1
```

Add default route for internet traffic:

```powershell
New-NetRoute -DestinationPrefix 0.0.0.0/0 -NextHop 192.168.10.1 -InterfaceAlias Ethernet -RouteMetric 256
```

### Verify Network Connectivity

Test connectivity to pfSense:

```powershell
ping 192.168.10.1
```

Test internet connectivity:

```powershell
ping 8.8.8.8
```

✅ Both must succeed before proceeding.

