## Install Active Directory Domain Services

### Install AD DS Role

Open PowerShell as Administrator:

```powershell
Install-WindowsFeature -Name AD-Domain-Services -IncludeManagementTools
```

This installs Active Directory Domain Services and management tools. Expect "Success: True" output after 2-3 minutes.

### Promote to Domain Controller

```powershell
Install-ADDSForest -DomainName corp.local -SafeModeAdministratorPassword (ConvertTo-SecureString "Lab@Secure2024!" -AsPlainText -Force) -Force -NoRebootOnCompletion
```

Creates new Active Directory forest `corp.local` and promotes DC01 to domain controller. Takes 3-5 minutes. Warnings about DNS delegation are normal.

### Restart Server

```powershell
Restart-Computer
```

Server reboots and loads all Active Directory services.

### Verify Active Directory

After reboot:

```powershell
Get-ADDomain
```

**Expected output:**

| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| **Name** | corp — domain short name |
| **Forest** | corp.local — full domain name |
| **PDCEmulator** | DC01.corp.local — DC01 is primary controller |
| **DomainMode** | Windows2016Domain — domain functional level |

