## Create Active Directory Structure

### Create Organizational Units

```powershell
New-ADOrganizationalUnit -Name "Staff" -Path "DC=corp,DC=local"
New-ADOrganizationalUnit -Name "IT_Admins" -Path "DC=corp,DC=local"
```

OUs are folders that organize users and computers by department.

### Create User Accounts

**John Smith:**

```powershell
New-ADUser -Name "John Smith" -GivenName "John" -Surname "Smith" -SamAccountName "jsmith" -UserPrincipalName "jsmith@corp.local" -Path "OU=Staff,DC=corp,DC=local" -AccountPassword (ConvertTo-SecureString "UserPass@123" -AsPlainText -Force) -Enabled $true
```

**Amy Jones:**

```powershell
New-ADUser -Name "Amy Jones" -GivenName "Amy" -Surname "Jones" -SamAccountName "ajones" -UserPrincipalName "ajones@corp.local" -Path "OU=Staff,DC=corp,DC=local" -AccountPassword (ConvertTo-SecureString "UserPass@123" -AsPlainText -Force) -Enabled $true
```

**Bob Wilson:**

```powershell
New-ADUser -Name "Bob Wilson" -GivenName "Bob" -Surname "Wilson" -SamAccountName "bwilson" -UserPrincipalName "bwilson@corp.local" -Path "OU=Staff,DC=corp,DC=local" -AccountPassword (ConvertTo-SecureString "UserPass@123" -AsPlainText -Force) -Enabled $true
```

### Create Security Group

```powershell
New-ADGroup -Name "Domain_Staff" -SamAccountName "Domain_Staff" -GroupCategory Security -GroupScope Global -Path "OU=Staff,DC=corp,DC=local"
```

### Add Users to Group

```powershell
Add-ADGroupMember -Identity "Domain_Staff" -Members "jsmith", "ajones", "bwilson"
```

